<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-1296 </DOCNO><TEXT>The invention deals with a process for the removal of sulfur dioxide fromwaste gases by catalytical conversion of the sulfur dioxide with oxygenand water on activated carbon of a grain size of 0.3 to 3.5 mm. The profitabilityof the process can considerably be improved by the use of relativelyfine-grained activated carbon with a high specific pressure loss andthus with a high space-time yield.</TEXT></DOC>